Ecuador's President Rafael Correa announced today that the creation of common citizenship is a goal in which "South America, in this case really, must learn from Europe."
Correa, who participated in the sixth presidential summit of the South American Union of Nations (Unasur) in Lima, told state-run TV Peru that Europeans "killed themselves in World War 2" and in other conflicts, "but now there are practically one homeland."
