In addition, Ecuador's president said he considered it "completely" a wish by his Colombian counterpart, Juan Manuel Santos, to negotiate with Nicaragua on the maritime borders between the two countries now, in the aftermath of the International Court in The Hague ruling, which ruled in favor of Nicaragua.
The judgment is not accepted at the moment.
"This is a problem between the South American and Central American countries.
