He also expressed hope in settling the dispute over the maritime border, which is being resolved in the same court of Peru and Chile, and expressed the view that "it is right for Latin America to seek international instances if the two countries commit to accept the judgment, however harsh it may be."
In the wake of the possibility that he will run in Ecuador's next presidential election to run for a third term, he noted that he perceives this possibility "with great optimism and joy, although sometimes it is very difficult."
